ependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"Hello,\nI'm working with pundit for the first time and like the [`permitted_attributes helper`](https://github.com/elabs/pundit#strong-parameters) as it bundles together (write) access control for actions and attributes.\nHowever, I now encounter the situation where I want to allow different sets of parameters for different actions.\nWould you consider adding such a feature if I prepared a pull request?\n\nMy idea is to extend permitted_attributes this way:\n\n``` ruby\ndef permitted_attributes(record)\n  name = record.class.to_s.demodulize.underscore\n  action_params_method = \"#{params[:action]}_attributes\"\n  attributes_method = policy(record).respond_to?(action_params_method) ?\n    action_params_method : :permitted_attributes\n  params.require(name).permit(*policy(record).send(attributes_method))\nend\n```\n","closed_by":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/varvet/pundit/issues/340/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/varvet/pundit/issues/340/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed"}